<title level="a">CHICAGO FROM 1880 TO 1890</title></bibl>
   </div>
  </front>
  <body>
   <p>An interesting group of figures has been compiled by this paper. We believe that forty years from now, 1930, Chicago will have at least a population of twenty million people. There will be at least a hundred-mile frontage, and let us say four hundred thousand buildings.</p>
   <p>If we did not have the following statistics, it would seem impossible:</p>
